<subSubSection pageId="232" pageNumber="837" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="232.[719,1311,2078,2539]" pageId="232" pageNumber="837">
Phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1225,2268,2302]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Epimys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="232" pageNumber="837" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="korinchi">R. korinchi</taxonomicName>
inRattus is unclear, although it might be related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[777,921,2355,2380]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Rattus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="232" pageNumber="837" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="baluensis">R.baluensis</taxonomicName>
, which it has been considered conspecific with. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
