<subSubSection pageId="232" pageNumber="837" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="232.[104,1309,2527,3483]" pageId="232" pageNumber="837">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[106,459,3178,3207]" pageId="232" pageNumber="837">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. There is virtually nothing known about the Sumatran Mountain Rat, and studies are required to fully understand it natural history, taxonomy, and threats. It does not seem to have any 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hatt" authorityYear="1934" box="[166,248,3291,3325]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Thamnomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="232" pageNumber="837" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">major</taxonomicName>
threats other than distributional restriction due to habitat loss in lowland areas surrounding its known distribution. It is found in Kerinci Seblat National Park and perhaps other protected areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
